						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Fragment of stone lying in the village Chāvaḍi.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1168.</p>						

						<p>The available details of the date in this damaged record are <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1090,</hi> and <hi rend="bold">Ās11vayuja, Paurṇamāsi, Thursday, lunar eclipse.</hi> The date corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1168, September 19, Thursday</hi> it the Śaka year is 1090 itself. The eclipse occurred on the previous day when the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> commenced after ·04.</p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record a gift on the first date to Dōra Jinā[laya]. It also registers a gift of land and income from taxes to god Svayaṁbhudēva, by Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara <hi rend="bold">Chauṇḍarasa</hi> of the <hi rend="bold">Silāhāra</hi> family on the occasion of a lunar eclipse.</p>						

						</summary>
